    <note>Zhou(1) Xingyi [16409] He died in battle with Jin. He was buried in Suzhou, Changshu county and his grandson (actually great grandson), Cai [16410], also a Changshu resident, was buried nearby. Cai's biography says that they were Jianning, Pucheng residents, who moved to Suzhou. However, the funerary inscription for descendant, Nanlao, notes moves from Runan to Chuzhou, Suichang county in ca. 318, i.e. beginning of Eastern Jin, then to Jianning, Pucheng at end of Tang, then to Daozhou at beginning of Song and then Xingyi(2) moved to Suzhou, Changshu county. YLDD, 2367.15a. CBD, 2, 1494.</note>
